    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CRH's PROFITS INCREASE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Brian Lavery</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Lavery, Brian</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>CRH PLC, Irish building materials company, reports first-half pretax profit of 180 million euros ($160 million), increase of 14 percent of year-earlier period and one that beats analysts' estimates; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Irish building materials company CRH P.L.C. reported first-half pretax profit of 180 million euros ($160 million), an increase of 14 percent over the comparable period of 1999, and one that beat analysts' estimates by about 5 million euros ($4.44 million). Earnings per share increased 21 percent, to 0.3726 euro.</p>
        <p>Brian Lavery (NYT)</p>
      </block>
